A blast at the Hilton hotel in Egypt's Taba resort killed or wounded over 100 people.
A second explosion was heard in Nuaiba, with suspicions of a car bomb attack.
Israeli tourists were among the casualties.
The Sinai Peninsula, a popular holiday spot, was targeted in a series of explosions.
Israeli officials warned of potential attacks, urging evacuation.
Despite previous alerts, the public was caught off guard.
The incidents underscored the ongoing security threats in the region, prompting swift rescue efforts and heightened vigilance.
